@@eSepulchur Pasture -- As Kowloon Sees It@@N

@@WTemple Circle, Funerary Doctrine Comparative Study@@N

Midgaard's burial crisis is not ours. But the Temple Circle reads it
as a @@rwarning written in bone@@N, because Kowloon processes its own
dead, and the failure modes are transferable.

The field was once the @@dNinth Acre@@N, where shepherd-priests rang a
bell at dusk to guide the lost. The Courier Lantern Office recognizes
this: @@ea signal maintained for the vulnerable@@N. Our Lampkeeper
tradition descends from the same impulse -- beacons guiding night
fishermen through shifting channels. @@yThis is the root of civic
duty.@@N

Then Midgaard scaled the mercy. Road dead were routed to the acre.
Names copied from signet rings. The old field became @@ySepulchur
Pasture@@N, where mercy became machine. The Temple Circle sees the
inflection: @@ywhen naming the dead becomes process rather than duty,
the dead become inventory@@N.

The @@yTithe of Last Burdens@@N imposed a burial tariff. Those who could
pay bought sanctified plots. Those who could not were entered as
@@d"deferred names"@@N in common furrows. The Temple Circle condemns this.
In Kowloon, @@yevery death receives a name before the next dawn@@N.
Deferral is denial. We learned this when six hundred died in Yen-Mak
and the @@dAshfall Registry@@N was built so it would never recur.

The @@WViolet Compact's@@N containment doctrine spread to the pasture:
certain remains forbidden immediate burial, held in wardwire trenches
and witness lantern circles. The Compact called it safety. Temple
mourners called it trapping souls in limbo. @@rSafety that prevents
rites is abandonment wearing procedure's mask.@@N

Then the omen: the @@rgravebell rang twice for every pull@@N -- once from
the tower, once from beneath the furrows. The Courier Lantern Office
would track this with extreme attention. A bell answering itself is a
@@rsystem with unauthorized feedback@@N. In our signal network, doubled
lantern-flash means a relay is compromised. In Midgaard's pasture,
doubled bell means the dead maintain their own registry.

Ledger irregularities followed: names without bodies, bodies without
names, claim tokens duplicated. "Deferred name" stopped meaning
paperwork and started meaning @@runrest@@N. The Jade Magistracy reads
this as @@rinstitutional debt coming due@@N.

Children repeat at dusk: @@d"Pay the living, name the dead, and do
not let the bell count twice."@@N In Kowloon, we do not wait for the
bell to count twice. @@yWe name the dead before the lanterns go dark.@@N
